			<ns0:name>k...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112873510090665368075/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This is umbrealla bug for the &amp;quot;20% project in 80% project&amp;quot;.

Currently we have decoder.h/decoder_x86_32.rl/decoder_x86_64.rl which are used by decoder-test.c and produce output identical to objdump (for the instructions they accept).

The goal of the project is to create general-purpose decoder which can be used by other projects.

Goals:
- Produce output identical to objdump (both &amp;quot;-M intel&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;-M att&amp;quot;) for the valid instructions (instructions with no spurious prefixes)
- Produce output suitable for use in higher-level programs (structure per instruction instead of pure text)
- Reduce decoder-test.c
- Keep validator unchanged
Non-goals:
- Fastest Decoder in the West
- Output identical to objdump for the invalid instructions
